Tammy Petersen, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Two more businesses were&nbsp;targeted on Wednesday by armed robbers, following two mall robberies in Cape Town&nbsp;earlier in&nbsp;day.Four men&nbsp;robbed Espresso Bakery in Section Street, Paarden Eiland, at 09:50 and&nbsp;held up staff and fled with cash.Police spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana said the four&nbsp;got away from&nbsp;the scene in a white Mercedes Benz.In a separate incident in Athlone, a store was robbed earlier in the day.Rwexana said while police are aware of the incident, no case was opened.Claims of a robbery at Kenilworth Centre circulating on social media have been dismissed.However, police confirmed that a jewellery store was burgled overnight, and the thieves fled with an undisclosed amount of the merchandise.AthloneOn Wednesday morning at 08:30, shots were fired at Vangate Mall in Athlone in an attempted robbery.&nbsp;Shoppers and staff reported the shooting to the police who responded within minutes.The gunmen, however, had already&nbsp;managed to flee&nbsp;in a getaway car.Also at 08:30, two guards were accosted by four men as they were about to load money into an ATM at a bank in the N1 City Mall.The robbers fled in a red Mazda with an undisclosed amount of cash as well as the two officers&rsquo; guns.No shots were fired.Following&nbsp;claims of a &ldquo;lockdown&rdquo; at the shopping centre, mall spokesperson Anthea Oostendorf said shops were &ldquo;up and running&rdquo; as normal. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.